  <span id="freeText14348271203395091248" style="display:none">'It's simply not in the nature of these [food] companies to care about the consumer in an empathic way. Making money is the sole reason they exist--or so says Wall Street.'<br /><br />So if you are concerned about your health or what is in the food you and your family eat, this is a great place to start to educate yourself about the amount of sugar, fat and salt that is in processed foods and why they are used. <br /><br />Over the past year, I began worrying about the amount of the unpronounceable chemicals that are in our foods, but maybe simply looking at how much sugar, fat and salt are included per serving will eliminate most of the bad choices on the shelves. Eat real, America!</span>
